description.p:
PPE: a poly(2,6-dimethyl-1,4-phenylene ether) with an intrinsic viscosity of 45 ml/g as measured in toluene at 25 (degree)  C. and a concentration of 0.6 gram per 100 ml;


PA-6: a polyamide-6 with a viscosity of 54-62 ml/g according to ASTM D789 in a solution of 8.4% by weight of nylon in 90% Formic Acid and an amine endgroup number of 72  MU eq./g.;


CAH: citric acid monohydrate;


SEBS: polystyrene-poly(ethylene-butylene)-polystyrene block copolymer;
